---
import BaseLayout from '../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';

const effectiveDate = 'June 9, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service"
  description="The terms and conditions governing your use of the SaltGrass Modular website and the information provided on it."
>
  <section class="py-section-y bg-ink-50 border-b border-ink-200">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl">
      <nav class="text-sm text-ink-600 mb-4" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-brand-primary">Home</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <span class="text-ink-900 font-semibold">Terms of Service</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-ink-900">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-ink-600 mt-3">Effective {effectiveDate}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="py-section-y bg-white">
    <div class="container max-w-3xl prose prose-ink prose-headings:font-display prose-headings:text-ink-900 prose-p:text-ink-700 prose-li:text-ink-700 prose-a:text-brand-primary">
      <p>
        These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of the SaltGrass Modular website (the "Site").
        By accessing or using the Site, you agree to these Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Use of the Site</h2>
      <p>
        You may use the Site for lawful purposes only. You agree not to use the Site in any way that
        could damage, disable, or impair it, or interfere with anyone else's use of it.
      </p>

      <h2>Information and Estimates</h2>
      <p>
        Content on this Site — including pricing ranges, timelines, models, and specifications — is
        provided for general informational purposes. Pricing and availability are estimates and may
        vary based on your specific project, location, site conditions, and material costs. Nothing on
        this Site constitutes a binding offer. Final pricing and terms are established in a written
        agreement for your specific project.
      </p>

      <h2>Quotes and Consultations</h2>
      <p>
        Submitting a quote or consultation request does not create a contract or obligation to purchase.
        Any project agreement will be set out in a separate written contract signed by both parties.
      </p>

      <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        All content on this Site — including text, graphics, logos, and images — is the property of
        SaltGrass Modular or its licensors and is protected by applicable intellectual property laws.
        You may not reproduce or distribute it without our written permission.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>
        The Site may contain links to third-party websites. We are not responsible for the content,
        policies, or practices of any third-party sites.
      </p>

      <h2>Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, express or implied. We do not
        warrant that the Site will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free of harmful components. Project
        warranties, where applicable, are governed by your written project agreement.
      </p>

      <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent permitted by law, SaltGrass Modular shall not be liable for any indirect,
        incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of the Site.
      </p>

      <h2>Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Oklahoma, without regard to its conflict
        of law provisions.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to These Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms from time to time. Continued use of the Site after changes are posted
        constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:Dylan.Walker@saltgrassmodular.com">Dylan.Walker@saltgrassmodular.com</a></li>
        <li>Phone: <a href="tel:+14056591949">(405) 659-1949</a></li>
        <li>Location: Oklahoma City, Oklahoma</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
